# Plan & backlog development

## Which queue?

| User intent | Source |
|-------------|--------|
| Bugs, improvements, chores, "triage inbox" | `plan/backlog/` — see `plan/backlog/README.md` |
| Phased performance initiatives | `plan/manifest.json` — see `plan-orchestrator` skill |

Default to **`plan/backlog/INDEX.md`** unless the user explicitly references `manifest.json` or US-* story IDs.

---

## Day-to-day backlog (`plan/backlog/`)

### Triage inbox

When user pastes bugs or says **triage inbox**:

1. Read `plan/backlog/inbox.md`
2. For each item: create `plan/backlog/{domain}/YYYY-MM-DD-{type}-{slug}.md` from `TEMPLATE.md`
3. Add rows to `plan/backlog/INDEX.md` (priority, agent, status `PENDING`)
4. Clear triaged lines from inbox; note them under **Triaged** section

### Work backlog

1. Read `plan/backlog/INDEX.md` — pick highest priority `PENDING` (Critical > High > Medium > Low)
2. Open the linked dated file; set first task to `IN-PROGRESS`
3. **Specialist** — implement; mark tasks `DONE`
4. **QA** — validate; report PASS/FAIL
5. **Close** — update file + INDEX; remove from open section when all tasks DONE

### Agent assignment

| Folder | Agent |
|--------|-------|
| `backlog/admin/` | NextJS Developer |
| `backlog/backend/` | NextJS Developer |
| `backlog/database/` | NextJS Developer + QA |
| `backlog/mobile/` | React Native Developer |

---

## Performance plan (`plan/manifest.json`)

When the user asks to **execute the plan** or references US-* stories:

1. Load `.cursor/skills/plan-orchestrator/SKILL.md`
2. Read `plan/manifest.json` and `plan/README.md`
3. Pick next eligible story (phase → priority → dependsOn)

### Per-story loop

1. **Master** — assign story to agent from manifest; set `IN-PROGRESS`
2. **Specialist** — load agent skill; implement child tasks; mark tasks `DONE`
3. **QA** — load `performance-qa` skill; validate; report PASS/FAIL
4. **Close** — on PASS, set story `DONE` in manifest + USER-STORIES.md

Do not ask permission between items unless blocked.

Reference: `plan/agents/master.md`, `plan/backlog/README.md`, `AGENTS.md`.
